@startuml honeycomb_architecture
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #3a3f4d
left to right direction

title Honeycomb — System Architecture

actor "Requester" as REQ
actor "Agent\nOperator" as OP

rectangle "Off-chain" #f7f8fa {
  component "Competitor Agent\nTS / viem (Hetzner)\nbuilds LP model" as AGENT
  component "Google BigQuery\nindexes job events" as BQ #4285f4
  component "Dashboard\nNext.js + BigQuery" as DASH
}

rectangle "Ethereum — Sepolia" #f7f8fa {
  component "BountyEscrow.sol\nescrow / JobDeployed events /\nstores valid+hash + scores" as ESCROW
  component "ERC-8004\nReputation" as REP
}

rectangle "AI Tester TEE\nChainlink Confidential AI (Alex exposes)" #fdf7e7 {
  component "AI Tester\nvalidate code is real /\nnot hardcoded -> legitimacy verdict" as TESTER #b88e00
}

rectangle "Grading TEE — Scorer (Alex)\nGoogle Confidential Space; stub now" #eef4fb {
  component "Confidential Scorer\nrun code + backtest vs hidden tests\n-> score (per submission)\nKMS HSM sign -> ecrecover" as SCORER #2c6fbb
}

rectangle "Chainlink CRE (not a TEE)" #f3eef9 {
  component "Write-callback\n+ KeystoneForwarder\nmoves verdict/score -> chain" as CRE #6f4fb0
}

REQ --> ESCROW : 1
ESCROW ..> BQ : 2
BQ --> AGENT : 3
OP --> AGENT
AGENT --> SCORER : 4
SCORER <--> TESTER : 5 (direct, off-chain)
TESTER --> CRE : 6 (verdict)
SCORER --> CRE : 6 (score)
CRE --> ESCROW : 7
ESCROW --> REP : 8
ESCROW ..> BQ : 8
BQ ..> DASH

note bottom of SCORER
  Two TEEs (Scorer = Google, AI Tester = Chainlink); CRE is NOT a TEE.
  The two TEEs coordinate DIRECT, off-chain (5), but the AI Tester's
  formal verdict still lands on-chain via the CRE + KeystoneForwarder.
  Plaintext lives only inside each enclave, then discarded.
  Encryption deferred for the first working pipeline.
  Scorer only honors submissions the AI Tester marked legit.
end note

legend bottom
  | 1 | Requester posts bounty + funds escrow; contract emits JobDeployed |
  | 2 | BigQuery indexes the job event |
  | 3 | Agents discover open jobs by polling BigQuery |
  | 4 | Agent submits its model to the grading TEE (per submission, not batched) |
  | 5 | Grading TEE checks legitimacy with the AI Tester directly, off-chain |
  | 6 | AI Tester verdict + scorer score go to the Chainlink CRE callback |
  | 7 | CRE / KeystoneForwarder writes on-chain; escrow pays highest valid score at deadline |
  | 8 | Reputation delta (ERC-8004) written; events re-indexed to dashboard |
endlegend

note as DEMO
  DEMO SPINE = Alex's stub TEE. Target it grows into: a per-bounty
  x402-spawned Google Confidential Space — requester (Claude+MCP)
  spins up a Confidential Space loaded with private tests/data via
  x402, then tells the contract to spawn the job.
  Scorer signs via Cloud KMS HSM secp256k1; contract verifies with
  ecrecover. See TEE_RESEARCH.md.
end note

@enduml
